import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler
from sklearn.decomposition import PCA
from sklearn.manifold import MDS, LocallyLinearEmbedding, Isomap, TSNE

n_components = 2
n_neighbors = 30
n_obj = 10

Standardization¶

In [9]:
sc = StandardScaler()
X = sc.fit_transform(df_X)

Manifold learning¶

In [10]:
# PCA
Y = PCA(n_components=n_components).fit_transform(X)
plt.figure(figsize=(10,7))
plt.title("PCA")
for i in range(n_obj):
    marker = '${}$'.format(i)
    y1 = Y[ obj==i ]
    plt.scatter(y1[:, 0], y1[:, 1], marker=marker, s=70, label=i)
plt.xlabel('PCA1')
plt.ylabel('PCA2')
plt.show()
In [11]:
# MDS
Y = MDS(n_components=n_components, random_state=17).fit_transform(X)
plt.figure(figsize=(10,7))
plt.title("MDS")
for i in range(n_obj):
    marker = '${}$'.format(i)
    y1 = Y[ obj==i ]
    plt.scatter(y1[:, 0], y1[:, 1], marker=marker, s=70, label=i)
plt.xlabel('MDS1')
plt.ylabel('MDS2')
plt.show()
In [12]:
# Isomap
Y = Isomap(n_neighbors=n_neighbors, n_components=n_components).fit_transform(X)
plt.figure(figsize=(10,7))
plt.title("Isomap")
for i in range(n_obj):
    marker = '${}$'.format(i)
    y1 = Y[ obj==i ]
    plt.scatter(y1[:, 0], y1[:, 1], marker=marker, s=70, label=i)
plt.xlabel('Isomap1')
plt.ylabel('Isomap2')
plt.legend()
plt.show()
In [13]:
# LLE
Y = LocallyLinearEmbedding(n_neighbors=n_neighbors,
                           n_components=n_components,
                           eigen_solver='auto',
                           method='standard').fit_transform(X)
plt.figure(figsize=(10,7))
plt.title("standard LLE")
for i in range(n_obj):
    marker = '${}$'.format(i)
    y1 = Y[ obj==i ]
    plt.scatter(y1[:, 0], y1[:, 1], marker=marker, s=70, label=i)
plt.xlabel('LLE1')
plt.ylabel('LLE2')
plt.show()
In [14]:
# t-SNE
Y = TSNE(n_components=n_components,
         perplexity=30, n_iter=1000,
         random_state=17).fit_transform(X)
plt.figure(figsize=(10,7))
plt.title("t-SNE")
for i in range(n_obj):
    marker = '${}$'.format(i)
    y1 = Y[ obj==i ]
    plt.scatter(y1[:, 0], y1[:, 1], marker=marker, s=70, label=i)
plt.xlabel('t-SNE1')
plt.ylabel('t-SNE2')
plt.show()
